results.name: Number of primes between successive composite numbers.
link: Harvey P. Dale, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: a(7) = 0 since there are no primes between the 7th and the 8th composites (14 and 15).
mathematica: Composite[n_Integer] := FixedPoint[n + PrimePi[ # ] + 1 &, n + PrimePi[n] + 1]; Table[ PrimePi[Composite[n + 1]] - PrimePi[Composite[n]], {n, 105}] (* _Robert G. Wilson v_, Dec 20 2004 *)
Differences[Select[Range[300],CompositeQ]]-1 (* Requires Mathematica version 10 or later *) (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Apr 01 2021 *)
